HEADWORD: Chemise
<hw>Che*mise"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., shirt, fr. LL.
<ets>camisa</ets>, <ets>camisia</ets>, shirt, thin dress; cf. G.
<ets>hemd</ets>, or OIr. <ets>caimmse</ets> sort of garment. Cf.
<er>Camis</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A shift, or undergarment, worn
by women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A wall that lines the face of a bank or
earthwork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chemisette</ent>⟦br⟧
